cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI 

This paper deals with logic and programming languages, which are typically categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the Curry-Howard correspondence, which relates logic and programming, and is often studied in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions parallel computation and communication, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
